{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Three years ago, I got a phone call, based on an earlier film I had made,"},{"time":4000,"text":"with an offer to embed the New Hampshire National Guard."},{"time":8000,"text":"My idea -- and literally, I woke up in the middle of the night,"},{"time":11000,"text":"and we've all have those moments. You know, you go to sleep --"},{"time":13000,"text":"I was excited, with this phone call."},{"time":16000,"text":"I was thinking, I just finished making another film about World War II vets,"},{"time":19000,"text":"and I realized I'd gotten to know their stories,"},{"time":21000,"text":"and I realized this was a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity"},{"time":25000,"text":"to tell a warrior's story as it unfolded."},{"time":27000,"text":"So I went to bed that night pretty excited."},{"time":30000,"text":"Not sure of all the details, but excited."},{"time":35000,"text":"It wasn't at four in the morning, but it was closer to midnight."},{"time":37000,"text":"Woke straight up. Wide-awake as could be."},{"time":39000,"text":"And I had this idea: what if I could, in effect, virtually embed,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and create a permeable relationship with the soldiers?"},{"time":45000,"text":"To tell the story from the inside out, versus the outside in?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":49000,"text":"So, I called back Major Heilshorn,"},{"time":51000,"text":"who's the public affairs officer of the New Hampshire National Guard."},{"time":53000,"text":"And he knew me, so I was like, \"Greg?\""},{"time":56000,"text":"He's like, \"Yes, Deborah?\""},{"time":58000,"text":"Told him my idea, and you know,"},{"time":61000,"text":"he is one of the bravest men in the world,"},{"time":63000,"text":"as is General Blair, who, in the end, gave me permission to try this experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":68000,"text":"Within 10 days, I was down at Fort Dix."},{"time":70000,"text":"He gave me my pick of units."},{"time":72000,"text":"I picked one unit -- Charlie Company, Third of the 172nd,"},{"time":75000,"text":"they're mountain infantry -- for two reasons."},{"time":77000,"text":"One, they're infantry."},{"time":79000,"text":"Number two, they were going to be based at LSA Anaconda,"},{"time":82000,"text":"so I knew they would have Internet access."},{"time":84000,"text":"The caveat for my access was I had to get the soldiers to volunteer."},{"time":86000,"text":"This was a big thing that"},{"time":88000,"text":"I think when Major H told me,"},{"time":90000,"text":"I wasn't really totally gathering what that would mean."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"So what that meant was, when I went down to Fort Dix,"},{"time":95000,"text":"I had to hop out in front of 180 guys and tell them of my vision."},{"time":99000,"text":"You can imagine the hailstorm of questions I got."},{"time":101000,"text":"The opening one was,"},{"time":103000,"text":"\"What the fuck do you know about the National Guard?\""},{"time":106000,"text":"I started with the 1607 Massachusetts Bay Colony Pequot Indian Wars."},{"time":111000,"text":"Gave them about a nine minute response,"},{"time":114000,"text":"and there we went."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"So, I'd like to show the clip of the film."},{"time":119000,"text":"It's our trailer, because I know, obviously you guys are busy,"},{"time":122000,"text":"many of you may not have had a chance to see it."},{"time":124000,"text":"So, I want to show the trailer,"},{"time":126000,"text":"and then I'm going to take apart one scene in detail."},{"time":129000,"text":"If we could roll?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138000,"text":"(Video) Stephen Pink: This is Sergeant Stephen Pink."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"Michael Moriarty: Specialist Michael Moriarty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"Zack Bazzi: Do I really want to go? Probably not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"Soldier: We're not supposed to talk to the media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"SP: I'm not the media, dammit!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":151000,"text":"MM: The day is here. Life will change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153000,"text":"Voice: The real deal, man! Narrator: You ready?"},{"time":155000,"text":"Soldier: Bring it on! Narrator: You ready? Voice 2: Iraq, here we come!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":161000,"text":"ZB: Every soldier eventually wants to go in combat."},{"time":163000,"text":"It's natural instinct."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164000,"text":"SP: If you let fear get to you,"},{"time":166000,"text":"then you're not going to be doing your job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"MM: Every single time you go out there, there's attacks."},{"time":170000,"text":"It's unbelievable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"ZB: Hey, Nestor, your ass crack is right in my face."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179000,"text":"Soldiers: IV! Are we on fire? IV!"},{"time":181000,"text":"Man down! Man down!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"MM: Keep going, brother. You wanna play?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"Michael Moriarty's Wife: It's really hard for him to not have his dad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"MM: This little kid is in the middle of a war zone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"Stephen Pink's Girlfriend: In the beginning, he's like, \"Write something dirty!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":201000,"text":"George W. Bush: The world's newest democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"MM: They're shooting at me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"SP: You don't put 150,000 troops in there,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and say we're there to create democracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213000,"text":"Soldier: We've got a drive through window at Burger King now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215000,"text":"SP: We're here to create money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217000,"text":"MM: I support George Bush. We're not there for the oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"Jon Baril: The worst thing in my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222000,"text":"SP: Baril, don't look at it, bud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224000,"text":"Michael Moriarty's Wife: He's not the same person anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":226000,"text":"MM: I will not go back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231000,"text":"Kevin Shangraw: The Iraqi people are who we are there to help --"},{"time":233000,"text":"and we just killed one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":234000,"text":"Soldiers: Sergeant Smith is down! Sergeant Smith is down?"},{"time":237000,"text":"There they are! Right there! Fire, fire!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":247000,"text":"JB: It'll be a better country in 20 years, 'cause we were there."},{"time":251000,"text":"I hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":263000,"text":"(Applause) Deborah Scranton: Thank you."},{"time":264000,"text":"One of the things I'd like to talk to you about"},{"time":267000,"text":"is having a conversation about something that is difficult to talk about."},{"time":271000,"text":"And I'd like to relate an experience I had here at TED."},{"time":274000,"text":"I don't know how many of you might imagine it,"},{"time":277000,"text":"but there's actually a TEDster who recently got back from Iraq."},{"time":282000,"text":"Paul? Come on, stand up."},{"time":284000,"text":"This is Paul Anthony."},{"time":286000,"text":"He served -- (Applause) -- with the Marines,"},{"time":291000,"text":"and I want to tell you a little, brief story."},{"time":295000,"text":"We were one of the lucky ones"},{"time":297000,"text":"to get in the class with the Sony cameras and the Vista software."},{"time":301000,"text":"Right? And we started talking."},{"time":302000,"text":"People will see my tag, and they'll see \"The War Tapes,\""},{"time":304000,"text":"and then we'll start talking about war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":306000,"text":"We got in a conversation with some other people in the class,"},{"time":310000,"text":"and it went on and on."},{"time":312000,"text":"I mean, we were there for an hour, talking."},{"time":314000,"text":"And it really highlighted something that I would like to ask"},{"time":316000,"text":"you guys to think about and hopefully to help with,"},{"time":320000,"text":"which is, I think a lot of us are very afraid to have conversations about war,"},{"time":323000,"text":"and about politics."},{"time":324000,"text":"And really -- because maybe we're going to disagree."},{"time":326000,"text":"Maybe it's going to get uncomfortable."},{"time":328000,"text":"How do we open it up to really be able to have a conversation?"},{"time":332000,"text":"And you know, Paul was talking,"},{"time":337000,"text":"and he then turned to Constance and said,"},{"time":340000,"text":"\"You know, I wouldn't have this conversation if she weren't here,"},{"time":343000,"text":"because I know she has my back.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":345000,"text":"And I want to say, I was nervous."},{"time":347000,"text":"Because I'm used to doing Q&amp;As."},{"time":349000,"text":"I really related to what James was saying yesterday,"},{"time":350000,"text":"because I'm behind the camera."},{"time":352000,"text":"You know, I can answer questions about my movie,"},{"time":354000,"text":"but for me to come up and talk for 18 minutes is a really long time."},{"time":356000,"text":"So, I wanted to say, Paul, I'm happy you're here,"},{"time":359000,"text":"because I know you have my back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"This film was not about the Internet,"},{"time":364000,"text":"but it could not have been made without it."},{"time":367000,"text":"The guys' tapes on average took two weeks to get from Iraq to me."},{"time":370000,"text":"In the meantime, the soldiers -- we would email and IM."},{"time":374000,"text":"I didn't save all of them,"},{"time":378000,"text":"because I didn't realize at the beginning"},{"time":380000,"text":"that it would be something that I would want to keep track of."},{"time":383000,"text":"But there were 3,211 emails and IMs and text messages"},{"time":388000,"text":"that I was able to save."},{"time":390000,"text":"The reason I quantify that is because we really embarked on this as a mutual journey"},{"time":397000,"text":"to really get inside of it."},{"time":399000,"text":"So I wanted to show you a clip,"},{"time":401000,"text":"and then I was going tell you a little bit of how it got put together."},{"time":404000,"text":"If we could roll the clip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":406000,"text":"(Video) SP: Today is sport. [Unclear] Radio: [Unclear] Christian soldiers."},{"time":409000,"text":"SP: We like to give these insurgents a fair chance."},{"time":413000,"text":"So, what we do, we ride with the windows down."},{"time":416000,"text":"Because, you know, we obviously have the advantage. I'm just kidding."},{"time":422000,"text":"We don't fucking ride with the goddam windows down."},{"time":425000,"text":"It's not true. Very unsafe."},{"time":431000,"text":"Whoa."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432000,"text":"Soldier: Right there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434000,"text":"SP: All right, let's get over to that site."},{"time":438000,"text":"Be advised, we're leaving Taji right now."},{"time":441000,"text":"We believe that the blast was right outside the gate of Taji,"},{"time":445000,"text":"we're heading to that location now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":449000,"text":"Soldier: That's a fucking car bomb!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":451000,"text":"Soldier: Motherfuckers!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":452000,"text":"Soldiers: Get your vest on!"},{"time":454000,"text":"Hey, get over the fucking -- yeah, yeah."},{"time":456000,"text":"Any one-four elements get to the gate!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":458000,"text":"SP: Sheriff one-six, or any one-four elements,"},{"time":461000,"text":"we need you at the gate of Taji right now, over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"Soldier: I'll walk you through it."},{"time":466000,"text":"(Voices)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":472000,"text":"SP: Stay low. Head over to the right."},{"time":475000,"text":"Get your bag, get your bag!"},{"time":479000,"text":"(Screams)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"SP: It was mass casualties."},{"time":486000,"text":"Probably 20 dead, at least 20 or 30 wounded Iraqis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":497000,"text":"SP: It just looked like, you know,"},{"time":499000,"text":"someone had thrown a quarter through a guy,"},{"time":501000,"text":"and it was just like -- there was no blood coming from the shrapnel wounds."},{"time":504000,"text":"Everything was cauterized,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and it was just like there was a void going through the body."},{"time":510000,"text":"This is the scene north."},{"time":514000,"text":"They just removed a burnt body, or half a body from here."},{"time":518000,"text":"I don't think there was anything left from his abdominal down."},{"time":525000,"text":"This is blood."},{"time":528000,"text":"And you know, you walk,"},{"time":530000,"text":"and you hear the pieces of skin."},{"time":535000,"text":"And that's it, that's all that's left."},{"time":538000,"text":"I remember giving three IVs, bandaging several wounded."},{"time":541000,"text":"Soldiers sitting in the corner of a sandbag wall, shaking and screaming."},{"time":546000,"text":"Medics who were terrified and couldn't perform."},{"time":550000,"text":"I later heard that Iraqi casualties were not to be treated in Taji."},{"time":556000,"text":"They can work on the post for pennies, but can't die there."},{"time":559000,"text":"They've got to die outside."},{"time":564000,"text":"If one of those incompetent medical officers told me to stop treatment,"},{"time":568000,"text":"I would've slit his throat right there."},{"time":581000,"text":"21:00 hours, and it's just our squad"},{"time":583000,"text":"going through today's events in our heads,"},{"time":586000,"text":"whether we want to or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":589000,"text":"News Anchor: More violence in Iraq."},{"time":591000,"text":"Twin suicide car bombings killed eight Iraqis and wounded dozens more"},{"time":595000,"text":"near a coalition base north of Baghdad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":597000,"text":"SP: We made the news."},{"time":598000,"text":"I feel exploited and proud at the same time."},{"time":600000,"text":"I've lost all faith in the media --"},{"time":602000,"text":"a hapless joke I would much rather laugh at than become a part of."},{"time":607000,"text":"I should really thank God for saving my lucky ass."},{"time":610000,"text":"I'll do that, then I'm gonna jerk off."},{"time":612000,"text":"Because these pages smell like Linds,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and there won't be any time for jerking off tomorrow."},{"time":617000,"text":"Another mission at 06:00."}]},{"cues":[{"time":623000,"text":"DS: Now -- (Applause) -- thanks."},{"time":627000,"text":"When I said earlier, to try and tell a story from the inside out, versus the outside in --"},{"time":632000,"text":"part of what Chris said so eloquently in his introduction -- is this melding."},{"time":637000,"text":"It's a new way of trying to make a documentary."},{"time":640000,"text":"When I met the guys, and 10 of them agreed to take cameras --"},{"time":644000,"text":"in total, 21 ended up filming."},{"time":646000,"text":"Five soldiers filmed the entire time."},{"time":648000,"text":"There are three featured in the film."}]},{"cues":[{"time":650000,"text":"The way I learned about Taji was Steve Pink sent me an email,"},{"time":654000,"text":"and in it, attached a photo of that burned body out at the car."},{"time":657000,"text":"And the tone from the email was,"},{"time":659000,"text":"you know, it had been a very bad day, obviously."},{"time":662000,"text":"And I saw in my IM window that Mike Moriarty was at the base."},{"time":666000,"text":"So, I pinged Mike and I said,"},{"time":668000,"text":"\"Mike, can you please go get that interview with Pink?\""},{"time":671000,"text":"Because the thing that very often is missing is,"},{"time":673000,"text":"in the military what they call \"hot wash.\""},{"time":675000,"text":"It's that immediate interview after something immediately happens, you know."},{"time":678000,"text":"And if you let time go by,"},{"time":680000,"text":"it kind of softens and smooths the edges."},{"time":682000,"text":"And for me, I really wanted that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":685000,"text":"So, in order to get the intimacy,"},{"time":687000,"text":"to share that experience with you, the guys --"},{"time":690000,"text":"the two most popular mounts --"},{"time":692000,"text":"there was a camera on the turret, the gun turret,"},{"time":694000,"text":"and then on the dashboard of the Humvee."},{"time":696000,"text":"Most of the Humvees, we ended up mounting two cameras in them."},{"time":701000,"text":"So you get to experience that in real time, right?"},{"time":705000,"text":"The interview that you see is the one that Mike went and did"},{"time":709000,"text":"within 24 hours of that episode happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712000,"text":"Steve Pink reading his journal"},{"time":714000,"text":"happened five months after he came home."},{"time":716000,"text":"I knew about that journal, but it was very, very private."},{"time":718000,"text":"And you know, you earn someone's trust,"},{"time":721000,"text":"especially in doc filmmaking, through your relationship."},{"time":724000,"text":"So, it wasn't until five months after he was home"},{"time":727000,"text":"that he would read that journal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729000,"text":"Now, the news footage I put in there to try to show --"},{"time":733000,"text":"you know, I think mainstream media tries to do the best they can"},{"time":737000,"text":"in the format that they have."},{"time":739000,"text":"But the thing that I know you all have heard a lot of times,"},{"time":741000,"text":"American soldiers saying,"},{"time":743000,"text":"\"Why don't they talk about the good stuff that we do?\""},{"time":745000,"text":"OK, this is a perfect example."},{"time":748000,"text":"Pink's squad and another squad spent their entire day outside the wire."},{"time":752000,"text":"They didn't have to go outside the wire."},{"time":754000,"text":"There were not Americans hurt out there."},{"time":756000,"text":"They spent their entire day outside the wire trying to save Iraqi lives --"},{"time":761000,"text":"the Iraqis who work on the post."},{"time":763000,"text":"So, when you may hear soldiers complaining,"},{"time":766000,"text":"that's what they're talking about, you know?"},{"time":768000,"text":"And I think it's such an amazing gift that they would share this"},{"time":772000,"text":"as a way of bridging."}]},{"cues":[{"time":774000,"text":"And when I talk about that polarity I get at so many different Q&amp;As,"},{"time":779000,"text":"and people are really opinionated."},{"time":781000,"text":"But it seems like people don't want to hear so much,"},{"time":783000,"text":"or listen, or try to have an exchange."},{"time":785000,"text":"And I'm as fiery as the next person, but I really think --"},{"time":788000,"text":"you know, different speakers have talked about their concern for the world,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and my concern is that we have to have these conversations."},{"time":796000,"text":"And we have to be able to go into scary places where we may, you know,"},{"time":800000,"text":"we think we know."},{"time":802000,"text":"But we just have to leave that little bit of openness, to know."},{"time":806000,"text":"There's such a disconnect."},{"time":808000,"text":"And for me, it's trying to bridge that disconnect."},{"time":813000,"text":"I'll share one story."},{"time":815000,"text":"I get -- I'm often asked, you know, for me,"},{"time":817000,"text":"what have been some of the special moments from having worked on this film."},{"time":821000,"text":"And at screenings, inevitably --"},{"time":823000,"text":"you know, as I'm sure all of you obviously do speaking stuff --"},{"time":827000,"text":"usually you have people who hang around and want to ask you more questions."},{"time":831000,"text":"And usually, the first questions are,"},{"time":833000,"text":"\"Oh, what kind of cameras did you use?\""},{"time":835000,"text":"Or you know, these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":836000,"text":"But there's always a few guys, almost always, who are the last ones."},{"time":841000,"text":"And I've learned over time that those are always the soldiers."},{"time":845000,"text":"And they wait until pretty much everybody's gone."},{"time":849000,"text":"And for me, one of the most profound stories someone shared with me,"},{"time":858000,"text":"that then became my story, was --"},{"time":860000,"text":"for those of you who haven't seen the film, and it's not a spoiler --"},{"time":865000,"text":"it's very common there are a lot of civilian accidents,"},{"time":867000,"text":"where people get in front of Humvees and they get killed."},{"time":870000,"text":"In this film, there is a scene where an Iraqi woman is killed."},{"time":875000,"text":"A soldier came up to me and stood, you know really, pretty close,"},{"time":882000,"text":"a foot away from me."},{"time":884000,"text":"He's a big guy."},{"time":886000,"text":"And he looked at me, and I smiled,"},{"time":888000,"text":"and then I saw the tears start welling up in his eyes."},{"time":893000,"text":"And he wasn't going to blink."},{"time":896000,"text":"And he said, \"My gunner was throwing candy.\""},{"time":899000,"text":"And I knew what he was going to say."},{"time":902000,"text":"The gunner was throwing candy."},{"time":905000,"text":"They used to throw candy to the kids."},{"time":908000,"text":"Kids got too close, very often."},{"time":911000,"text":"And he said, \"I killed a child."},{"time":914000,"text":"And I'm a father. I have children."},{"time":918000,"text":"I haven't been able to tell my wife."},{"time":920000,"text":"I'm afraid she's going to think I'm a monster.\""},{"time":927000,"text":"I hugged him, of course,"},{"time":929000,"text":"and I said, you know, \"It's going to be OK.\""},{"time":931000,"text":"And he said, \"I'm going to bring her to see your film."},{"time":934000,"text":"And then I'm going to tell her.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"So when I talk about a disconnect,"},{"time":947000,"text":"it's not only for maybe those people who don't know a soldier,"},{"time":950000,"text":"which there obviously are. You know, these days,"},{"time":952000,"text":"it's not like World War II, where there was a war front and a home front,"},{"time":955000,"text":"and everybody seemed involved."},{"time":957000,"text":"You can go for days here and not feel like there's a war going on."},{"time":960000,"text":"And often, I'll hear people say,"},{"time":962000,"text":"who maybe know that I did this film,"},{"time":964000,"text":"and they say, \"Oh, you know, I'm against the war, but I support the soldiers.\""},{"time":971000,"text":"And I've started to ask them,"},{"time":974000,"text":"\"Well, that's nice. What are you doing?"},{"time":977000,"text":"Are you volunteering at a VA?"},{"time":980000,"text":"You go and see anybody?"},{"time":982000,"text":"Do you, if you find out your neighbor's been, do you spend some time?"},{"time":989000,"text":"Not necessarily ask questions, but see if they want to talk?"},{"time":993000,"text":"Do you give money to any of the charities?\""},{"time":995000,"text":"You know, obviously, like Dean Kamen's working on that amazing thing,"},{"time":998000,"text":"but there's charities where you can sponsor computers for wounded soldiers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1003000,"text":"I think, I challenge us to say --"},{"time":1008000,"text":"to operationalize those terms, when we say we support someone, you know?"},{"time":1011000,"text":"Are you a friend to them?"},{"time":1013000,"text":"Do you really care?"},{"time":1015000,"text":"And I would just say it's my hope, and I would ask you guys"},{"time":1019000,"text":"to please, you know, reach out a hand."},{"time":1025000,"text":"And really do give them a hug."},{"time":1029000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}